I'm not an expert, take this with a grain of salt.

Look into how PR firms operate. Specifically, where's your audience, and how can you put your content in front of them? Not (or not just) buying ads, but pitching stories to journalists, understanding networks of influence, researching how other comparable work got popular.

Are you going after furries? Which specific furries? Which specific non-furries? Where do they hang out? When your audience discovers a new game, where are they seeing it, and who's telling them? Are they reading curated reviews of lewd games somewhere? Are they running across them on FA, or on /trash/, or are they seeing high-scoring content on e621? Are they seeing your game linked in discord or twitter? How do you get that person to tell them other people about your game? Can you tap into furry drama somehow without alienating your fanbase? Is there a human-interest story you can pitch to a publication about your adventures in porn? Can you get virality by e.g. rewarding users who share your game with free content, or letting them share progress somehow? Is there some specific originating community where a lot of successful smut games come from?
